iasm (10%)\\r\\n\\r\\nBegin the interview now with your introduction.\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Hi! I\'m Sarah, and I\'ll be conducting your technical interview today for the Software Tester position. To start, could you briefly introduce yourself and tell me what excites you about this role?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"I am rinu, i have experience in php, jQuery and Mysql\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"Thanks for the introduction, Rinu! It\'s great to meet you.\\n\\nI see you have experience with PHP, jQuery, and MySQL. Could you walk me through a specific project where you used these technologies together? What was your role in that project?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"i have a project on e commerce, which for  a restaurant menu\"},{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":\"That sounds like an interesting project! For this e-commerce restaurant menu, how did you handle the testing process to ensure the menu items, pricing, and ordering functionality worked correctly?\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"For testing the e-commerce restaurant menu, I followed a mix of manual and functional testing approaches.\\r\\n\\r\\nFirst, I tested all menu items to ensure they were displayed correctly with the right name, image, description, and price as per the database. I verified that any updates in the admin panel were reflected properly on the user side.\\r\\n\\r\\nThen, I tested the ordering functionality by placing multiple test orders \\u2014 adding items to the cart, updating quantities, removing items, and checking that the total price and taxes were calculated correctly.\\r\\n\\r\\nI also tested different user scenarios such as ordering as a guest and as a registered user, and validated form inputs like address and phone number.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor negative testing, I checked cases like empty cart submission, invalid input values, and network interruptions to ensure proper error handling.\\r\\n\\r\\nFinally, I tested the system across di